National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni in New York City to discuss regional developments. They talked about the humanitarian and economic costs of the ongoing conflict in South Sudan and agreed on the need for the international community and regional partners to work towards achieving peace. Rice expressed concern over the conflict in Sudan, particularly in Darfur, and the bombing of civilians in Southern Kordofan and Blue Nile States. They also discussed efforts to defeat the Lord's Resistance Army and cooperation to support the African Union Mission in Somalia. Lastly, they talked about the collaboration between the United States and Uganda in countering terrorism and preventing violent extremism in the region.